{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_28973c886ffeuilhHEURLxpCND","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d768c4bd3001CHPQHSzbWdW4nr","parts":[{"id":"prt_d768c5538001qGsoeEChD96Z3z","messageID":"msg_d768c4bd3001CHPQHSzbWdW4nr","sessionID":"ses_28973c886ffeuilhHEURLxpCND","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9966e36d130a4651b6a99539","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md"},"output":"<path>/workspace/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: <div align=\"center\">\n2:     <img src=\"docs/assets/meerkat_banner.png\" height=100 alt=\"Meerkat logo\"/>\n3: \n4: ---\n5: \n6: <!-- ![GitHub Workflow Status](https://github.com/HazyResearch/meerkat/actions/workflows/.github/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg) -->\n7: [![GitHub](https://img.shields.io/github/license/HazyResearch/meerkat)](https://img.shields.io/github/license/HazyResearch/meerkat)\n8: [![pre-commit](https://img.shields.io/badge/pre--commit-enabled-brightgreen?logo=pre-commit&logoColor=white)](https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit)\n9: \n10: Create interactive views of any dataset.\n11: \n12: [**Website**](http://meerkat.wiki)\n13: | [**Quickstart**](http://meerkat.wiki/docs/start/quickstart-df.html)\n14: | [**Docs**](http://meerkat.wiki/docs/index.html)\n15: | [**Contributing**](CONTRIBUTING.md)\n16: | [**Discord**](https://discord.gg/pw8E4Q26Tq)\n17: | [**Blogpost**](https://hazyresearch.stanford.edu/blog/2023-03-01-meerkat)\n18: \n19: </div>\n20: \n21: \n22: ## ⚡️ Quickstart\n23: \n24: ```bash\n25: pip install meerkat-ml\n26: ```\n27: <!-- \n28: > **_GPU Install_**: If you want to use Meerkat with a GPU, you will need to install PyTorch with GPU support. See [here](https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/) for more details. -->\n29: \n30: <!-- ```bash\n31: pip install \"meerkat-ml @ git+https://github.com/robustness-gym/meerkat@clever-dev\"\n32: ```  -->\n33: <!-- \n34: > **_Optional Dependencies_**: some parts of Meerkat rely on optional dependencies e.g. audio processing may rely on utilities from `torchaudio`. See  -->\n35: <!-- \n36: Then try one of our demos,\n37: \n38: ```bash\n39: mk demo tutorial-image-gallery --copy\n40: ```\n41: \n42: Explore the code for this demo in `tutorial-image-gallery.py`. To see a full list of demos, use `mk demo --help`.  -->\n43: \n44: **Next Steps**.\n45: Check out our [Getting Started page](http://meerkat.wiki/docs/start/quickstart-df.html) and our [documentation](http://meerkat.wiki/docs/index.html) to start building with Meerkat.\n46: \n47: ## Why Meerkat?\n48: \n49: Meerkat is an open-source Python library that helps users visualize, explore, and annotate any dataset. It is especially useful when processing unstructured data types (_e.g._ free text, PDFs, images, video) with machine learning models. \n50: \n51: ### ✏️ Features and Design Principles\n52: \n53: Here are four principles that inform Meerkat's design.\n54: \n55: **(1) Low overhead.**  With four lines of Python, start interacting with any dataset. \n56: - Zero-copy integrations with your preferred data abstractions: Pandas, Arrow, HF Datasets, Ibis, SQL.\n57: - Limited data movement. With Meerkat, you interact with your data where it already lives: no uploads to external databases and no reformatting.\n58: \n59: ```python\n60: import meerkat as mk\n61: df = mk.from_csv(\"paintings.csv\")\n62: df[\"image\"] = mk.files(\"image_url\")\n63: df\n64: ```\n65: \n66: <div align=\"center\">\n67:   <img src=\"website/static/dataframe-demo.gif\" height=300 alt=\"Meerkat logo\"/>\n68: </div>\n69: \n70: \n71: **(2) Diverse data types.** Visualize and annotate almost any data type in Meerkat interfaces: text, images, audio, video, MRI scans, PDFs, HTML, JSON. \n72: \n73: <div align=\"center\">\n74: \t<img src=\"website/static/data-types.gif\" height=300 alt=\"\"/>\n75: </div>\n76: \n77: \n78: **(3) \"Intelligent\" user interfaces.** Meerkat makes it easy to embed **machine learning models** (e.g. LLMs) within user interfaces to enable intelligent functionality such as searching, grouping and autocomplete. \n79: \n80: ```python\n81: df[\"embedding\"] = mk.embed(df[\"img\"], engine=\"clip\")\n82: match = mk.gui.Match(df,\n83: \tagainst=\"embedding\",\n84: \tengine=\"clip\"\n85: )\n86: sorted_df = mk.sort(df,\n87: \tby=match.criterion.name,\n88: \tascending=False\n89: )\n90: gallery = mk.gui.Gallery(sorted_df)\n91: mk.gui.html.div([match, gallery])\n92: ```\n93: \n94: <div align=\"center\">\n95: \t<img src=\"website/static/interact-demo.gif\" height=300 alt=\"Meerkat logo\"/>\n96: </div>\n97: \n98: **(4) Declarative (think: Seaborn), but also infinitely customizable and composable.**\n99: Meerkat visualization components can be composed and customized to create new interfaces. \n100: \n101: ```python\n102: plot = mk.gui.plotly.Scatter(df=plot_df, x=\"umap_1\", y=\"umap_2\",)\n103: \n104: @mk.gui.reactive\n105: def filter(selected: list, df: mk.DataFrame):\n106:     return df[df.primary_key.isin(selected)]\n107: \n108: filtered_df = filter(plot.selected, plot_df)\n109: table = mk.gui.Table(filtered_df, classes=\"h-full\")\n110: \n111: mk.gui.html.flex([plot, table], classes=\"h-[600px]\") \n112: ```\n113: \n114: <div align=\"center\">\n115: \t<img src=\"website/static/compose.gif\" height=300 alt=\"Meerkat logo\"/>\n116: </div>\n117: \n118: \n119: ### ✨ Use cases where Meerkat shines\n120: - _Exploratory analysis over unstructured data types._ [Demo](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=a8FBT33QACQ)\n121: - _Spot-checking the behavior of large language models (e.g. GPT-3)._  [Demo](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3ItA70qoe-o)\n122: - _Identifying systematic errors made by machine learning models._ [Demo](https://youtu.be/4Kk_LZbNWNs)\n123: - _Rapid labeling of validation data._\n124: \n125: ### 🤔 Use cases where Meerkat may not be the right fit\n126: \n127: - _Are you only working with structured data (e.g. numerical and categorical variables)?_ Popular data visualization libraries (_e.g._ [Seaborn](https://seaborn.pydata.org/), [Matplotlib](https://matplotlib.org/)) are often sufficient. If you're looking for interactivity, [Plotly](https://plotly.com/) and [Streamlit](https://streamlit.io/) work well with structured data. Meerkat is differentiated in how it visualizes unstructured data types: long-form text, PDFs, HTML, images, video, audio...  \n128: - _Are you trying to make a straightforward demo of a machine learning model (single input/output, chatbot) and share with the world?_ [Gradio](https://gradio.app/) is likely a better fit! Though, if your demo involves visualizing lots of data, you may find Meerkat useful.\n129: - _Are you trying to manually label tens of thousands of data points?_  If you are looking for a data labeling tool to use with a labeling team, there are great open source labeling solutions designed for this (_e.g._ [LabelStudio](https://labelstud.io/)). In contrast, Meerkat is great fit for teams/individuals without access to a large labeling workforce who are using pretrained models (_e.g._ GPT-3) and need to label validation data or in-context examples.\n130: \n131: \n132: \n133: \n134: <!-- Our goal is to make foundation models a more reliable\n135: software abstraction for processing unstructured datasets.\n136: [Read our blogpost to learn more.](https://hazyresearch.stanford.edu/blog/2023-03-01-meerkat)\n137:  -->\n138: \n139: \n140: \n141: ## ✉️ About\n142: \n143: Meerkat is being built by Machine Learning PhD students in the [Hazy Research](https://hazyresearch.stanford.edu) lab at Stanford. We're excited to build for a future where models will make it easier for teams to sift and reason through large volumes of unstructtured data effortlessly. \n144: \n145: Please reach out to `kgoel [at] cs [dot] stanford [dot] edu, eyuboglu [at] stanford [dot] edu, and arjundd [at] stanford [dot] edu` if you would like to use Meerkat for a project, at your company or if you have any questions.\n\n(End of file - total 145 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<div align=\"center\">\n    <img src=\"docs/assets/meerkat_banner.png\" height=100 alt=\"Meerkat logo\"/>\n\n---\n\n<!-- ![GitHub Workflow Status](https://github.com/HazyResearch/meerkat/actions/workflows/.github/workflows/ci.yml/badge.svg) -->\n[![GitHub](https://img.shields.io/github/license/HazyResearch/meerkat)](https://img.shields.io/github/license/HazyResearch/meerkat)\n[![pre-commit](https://img.shields.io/badge/pre--commit-enabled-brightgreen?logo=pre-commit&logoColor=white)](https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit)\n\nCreate interactive views of any dataset.\n\n[**Website**](http://meerkat.wiki)\n| [**Quickstart**](http://meerkat.wiki/docs/start/quickstart-df.html)\n| [**Docs**](http://meerkat.wiki/docs/index.html)\n| [**Contributing**](CONTRIBUTING.md)\n| [**Discord**](https://discord.gg/pw8E4Q26Tq)\n| [**Blogpost**](https://hazyresearch.stanford.edu/blog/2023-03-01-meerkat)\n\n</div>\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.md","time":{"start":1775810402028,"end":1775810402039}}}]}
